1
00:01:30,340 --> 00:01:31,171
[door closes]

2
00:01:31,258 --> 00:01:32,123
How was my speech?

3
00:01:32,217 --> 00:01:33,423
You were brilliant.

4
00:01:33,510 --> 00:01:35,171
-[Anne] Did I lisp?
- You don't lisp.

5
00:01:35,262 --> 00:01:36,844
I know.
That was what was so troubling about it.

6
00:01:36,930 --> 00:01:39,012
- The thought that I suddenly did.
- No.

7
00:01:39,516 --> 00:01:41,257
Sarah, you must say hello
to the little ones.

8
00:01:41,351 --> 00:01:43,592
No. It is macabre.

9
00:01:44,354 --> 00:01:45,344
[Anne] Please.

10
00:01:45,814 --> 00:01:46,724
[Sarah] No.

11
00:01:46,815 --> 00:01:48,601
I love you, but that I will not do.

12
00:01:48,692 --> 00:01:50,353
-[Anne] If you love me...
- Love has limits.

13
00:01:50,444 --> 00:01:51,730
It should not.

14
00:01:52,404 --> 00:01:53,394
[keys jingling]

15
00:01:53,488 --> 00:01:55,274
[lock turning]

16
00:02:18,639 --> 00:02:21,427
You do not lisp, but you are mad.

17
00:02:21,516 --> 00:02:22,802
Giving me a palace?

18
00:02:23,769 --> 00:02:26,386
I've been wanting to give you something
for quite some time now.

19
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:29,142
Seemed like the perfect opportunity
with Marlborough winning.

20
00:02:29,232 --> 00:02:32,475
It is a monstrous extravagance,
Mrs. Morley. We are at war.

21
00:02:32,569 --> 00:02:33,730
We won.

22
00:02:33,820 --> 00:02:35,857
It is not over. We must continue.

23
00:02:36,948 --> 00:02:37,938
Oh.

24
00:02:38,700 --> 00:02:39,815
Oh, I did not know that.

25
00:02:40,619 --> 00:02:42,610
[crow cawing]

26
00:02:52,381 --> 00:02:54,372
[classical music playing]

27
00:03:16,530 --> 00:03:17,895
[knocking on door]

28
00:03:18,699 --> 00:03:20,565
[footsteps]

29
00:03:37,676 --> 00:03:38,791
[woman] Take a hunk of bread.

30
00:03:42,055 --> 00:03:45,389
And then Sally will take you to clean up
and then to Her Ladyship.

31
00:04:01,950 --> 00:04:03,361
[woman] This mud stinks.

32
00:04:04,202 --> 00:04:05,658
[Sally] They shit in the streets
round here.

33
00:04:06,371 --> 00:04:07,907
â€œPolitical commentary," they call it.

34
00:04:08,373 --> 00:04:09,363
Go through here.

35
00:04:09,458 --> 00:04:10,368
Clean yourself up.

36
00:04:11,543 --> 00:04:12,533
Thank you so much.

37
00:04:18,467 --> 00:04:20,799
-[billiards balls clacking]
-[indistinct chatter]

38
00:04:22,179 --> 00:04:23,169
Lady Marlborough.

39
00:04:24,765 --> 00:04:26,802
I didn't know the new sewer ended in here.

40
00:04:27,726 --> 00:04:29,842
It is I, Abigail.

41
00:04:30,896 --> 00:04:31,931
Dear cousin.

42
00:04:32,939 --> 00:04:34,350
I have a letter from our aunt...

43
00:04:35,358 --> 00:04:36,348
and...

44
00:04:38,570 --> 00:04:40,436
I'm sorry,
I did not mean to present as a...

45
00:04:41,490 --> 00:04:43,151
I fell out of a carriage.

46
00:04:45,494 --> 00:04:46,325
[shrieks]

47
00:04:48,705 --> 00:04:49,695
And a man was pulling his...

48
00:04:53,752 --> 00:04:55,117
Never mind the man.

49
00:04:55,754 --> 00:04:56,835
The letter from our aunt.

50
00:04:58,340 --> 00:04:59,421
[flies buzzing]

51
00:04:59,925 --> 00:05:00,915
Friends of yours?

52
00:05:01,802 --> 00:05:03,042
I'm sorry.

53
00:05:03,678 --> 00:05:05,464
Your name, girl. If we are blood, name it.

54
00:05:05,555 --> 00:05:06,545
I did not?

55
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:08,506
- Abigail Hill.
-[Sarah] The Somerset Hills?

56
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:11,763
The one who went mad and burnt
his own house down, himself in it?

57
00:05:11,853 --> 00:05:13,685
Lost all his money at whist.

58
00:05:13,772 --> 00:05:15,308
No one bets on whist.

59
00:05:15,398 --> 00:05:16,888
My uncle was one of a kind.

60
00:05:16,983 --> 00:05:18,690
[Abigail] I apologize for my appearance.

61
00:05:18,777 --> 00:05:22,020
The staff led me here.
A harmless prank of some sort, I suspect.

62
00:05:22,113 --> 00:05:23,228
[Sarah] And you want...

63
00:05:23,657 --> 00:05:27,025
I hoped I might be employed here by you...
as something.

64
00:05:27,285 --> 00:05:29,526
A monster for the children
to play with, perhaps?

65
00:05:30,872 --> 00:05:31,953
Yes, if you like.

66
00:05:33,166 --> 00:05:34,076
[growls]

67
00:05:37,462 --> 00:05:38,543
[chuckles]

68
00:05:39,506 --> 00:05:42,498
[classical music playing]

69
00:05:56,648 --> 00:05:57,479
[bell rings]

70
00:05:57,566 --> 00:05:59,557
[muffled cheering]

71
00:06:12,622 --> 00:06:14,408
[cheering continues]

72
00:06:22,215 --> 00:06:23,922
[cheering stops]

73
00:06:29,806 --> 00:06:30,637
[music fades]

74
00:06:30,724 --> 00:06:31,634
A palace.

75
00:06:31,725 --> 00:06:34,683
You seem angry at my good fortune
and I thought we were friends.

76
00:06:34,769 --> 00:06:36,555
I really doubt you've made that mistake.

77
00:06:36,646 --> 00:06:38,853
I was actually just teasing.
I thought you'd see that.

78
00:06:39,566 --> 00:06:40,556
It will not stand.

79
00:06:41,192 --> 00:06:44,901
Well, it will if I build it
using the finest craftsmen in the land.

80
00:06:44,988 --> 00:06:46,570
I hope it will stand for 100 years

81
00:06:46,656 --> 00:06:48,613
as a symbol
of my husband's gallant victory.

82
00:06:48,992 --> 00:06:50,858
Listen, I applaud
your husband's gallant victory,

83
00:06:50,952 --> 00:06:52,943
but considering the parlous state
of the treasury,

84
00:06:53,038 --> 00:06:55,951
it seems something the queen should've
taken advice from her loyal opposition on.

85
00:06:56,041 --> 00:06:58,658
Oh, but then it would've lost
its delightful surprise element.

86
00:06:59,210 --> 00:07:00,245
Cunt!

87
00:07:00,587 --> 00:07:02,077
[man] Horatio has done it again.

88
00:07:02,172 --> 00:07:04,539
Prime Minister, we need to discuss
who will go to the French

89
00:07:04,633 --> 00:07:07,421
-with the peace treaty proposal.
- We do not need a peace treaty proposal.

90
00:07:07,510 --> 00:07:08,671
We have them on the run.

91
00:07:08,762 --> 00:07:10,002
So they will give in to us.

92
00:07:10,096 --> 00:07:11,586
One battle will not win the war.

93
00:07:11,681 --> 00:07:14,093
I have held my party together,
as we the country landowners

94
00:07:14,184 --> 00:07:15,970
have essentially paid
for this entire war--

95
00:07:16,061 --> 00:07:17,222
And grateful we are, too.

96
00:07:17,312 --> 00:07:19,519
...while city merchants
enrich themselves from it.

97
00:07:19,606 --> 00:07:23,816
And yet I do not see your fat tweedy dead
when I look out upon the battlefield.

98
00:07:23,902 --> 00:07:25,233
We're out of money. My point.

99
00:07:25,320 --> 00:07:27,778
The French are chastened,
but not defeated, Harley.

100
00:07:27,864 --> 00:07:29,275
We must destroy them.

101
00:07:29,366 --> 00:07:32,358
Make them sue for peace
with broken hearts and begging backs.

102
00:07:32,827 --> 00:07:35,364
- How sweet your wife is, Marlborough.
- Sweet and right.

103
00:07:35,455 --> 00:07:37,492
I cannot agree.
We must take it to the queen.

104
00:07:37,582 --> 00:07:40,074
If you'd be kind enough
to arrange a time, Lady Marlborough.

105
00:07:40,168 --> 00:07:40,999
[Sarah] Of course.

106
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:48,878
[snoring]

107
00:07:53,515 --> 00:07:55,005
[woman coughs]

108
00:08:22,460 --> 00:08:23,450
[exclaims]

109
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:35,512
I'm ready for the Russian ambassador.

110
00:08:36,808 --> 00:08:37,889
Who did your makeup?

111
00:08:37,976 --> 00:08:39,842
We went for something dramatic.
Do you like it?

112
00:08:40,770 --> 00:08:41,976
You look like a badger.

113
00:08:42,814 --> 00:08:43,679
Oh.

114
00:08:45,316 --> 00:08:47,728
[Sarah] Are you going to cry? Really?

115
00:08:48,820 --> 00:08:51,278
Well, what do you think you look like?

116
00:08:55,910 --> 00:08:56,900
A badger.

117
00:08:58,121 --> 00:09:01,239
Do you really think you can meet
the Russian delegation looking like that?

118
00:09:02,584 --> 00:09:03,415
No.

119
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:05,041
I will manage it.

120
00:09:06,212 --> 00:09:07,247
Get back to your rooms.

121
00:09:08,256 --> 00:09:09,246
Thank you.

122
00:09:18,475 --> 00:09:20,557
Did you just look at me? Did you?

123
00:09:21,144 --> 00:09:23,476
Look at me! Look at me!

124
00:09:23,563 --> 00:09:25,554
How dare you? Close your eyes!

125
00:09:41,873 --> 00:09:42,863
[Sally] Hello.

126
00:09:43,374 --> 00:09:44,284
Hello.

127
00:09:44,375 --> 00:09:46,707
Mrs. Meg says you are to scrub the floor

128
00:09:46,795 --> 00:09:49,127
until she can see
her toothless, fat face in it.

129
00:09:49,672 --> 00:09:50,662
Sorry.

130
00:10:17,033 --> 00:10:18,944
[gasps]

131
00:10:20,620 --> 00:10:21,655
You might need gloves.

132
00:10:22,288 --> 00:10:24,655
Lye is dangerous. It burns bad.

133
00:10:27,168 --> 00:10:28,658
[exclaims]

134
00:10:30,672 --> 00:10:33,289
[gasping]

135
00:10:35,301 --> 00:10:37,793
[moaning painfully]

136
00:10:40,723 --> 00:10:41,963
[Anne] Sarah!

137
00:10:42,058 --> 00:10:44,265
I'm here.

138
00:10:46,646 --> 00:10:49,479
You! Grab the bandage box off the shelf.

139
00:10:49,566 --> 00:10:51,807
The queen's had an attack of gout. Hurry!

140
00:11:09,544 --> 00:11:12,753
[Cries]

141
00:11:13,965 --> 00:11:15,251
[Sarah] Mrs. Meg, brandy.

142
00:11:19,429 --> 00:11:20,669
[Anne] It hurts.

143
00:11:20,763 --> 00:11:22,925
[Sarah] My dearest, I know.

144
00:11:24,851 --> 00:11:26,057
[moans]

145
00:11:28,771 --> 00:11:29,977
Cousin, the beef.

146
00:11:32,317 --> 00:11:33,523
[Sarah] Tell me a story.

147
00:11:34,027 --> 00:11:34,937
I can't.

148
00:11:35,195 --> 00:11:36,026
Ow!

149
00:11:36,112 --> 00:11:37,102
[Sarah] Gently.

150
00:11:39,199 --> 00:11:40,530
-[Anne] I can't.
-[Sarah] Yes, you can.

151
00:11:41,701 --> 00:11:42,782
Cousin, start wrapping.

152
00:11:44,412 --> 00:11:45,652
Everyone else, leave please.

153
00:11:47,999 --> 00:11:49,205
[whimpering]

154
00:11:50,668 --> 00:11:52,158
[Sarah] How we first met. Tell me that.

155
00:11:55,173 --> 00:11:59,132
The wretched Cheever boy
had me on the ground

156
00:11:59,219 --> 00:12:02,007
and he was holding me
and dropping spittle in my face.

157
00:12:02,096 --> 00:12:03,552
[Sarah] He is still a pig. Then what?

158
00:12:06,351 --> 00:12:08,262
[Anne sniffling]

159
00:12:09,062 --> 00:12:10,678
[Anne] And then I heard footsteps.

160
00:12:12,482 --> 00:12:13,688
Fast footsteps.

161
00:12:15,526 --> 00:12:16,561
<i>Ow, ow!</i>

162
00:12:19,155 --> 00:12:20,816
[birds chirping]

163
00:12:20,907 --> 00:12:23,945
And I saw these pink shoes
running towards me.

164
00:12:26,746 --> 00:12:28,077
And then they disappeared.

165
00:12:37,298 --> 00:12:38,834
And then I heard a crack.

166
00:12:40,385 --> 00:12:41,671
And then he fell off me.

167
00:12:45,265 --> 00:12:46,596
[Anne moans]

168
00:12:46,683 --> 00:12:50,221
And you held my hand and said,
â€œHello. I'm Sarah.

169
00:12:50,311 --> 00:12:52,643
You're covered in spittle.
Let's wash you off."

170
00:12:56,484 --> 00:12:57,724
[Anne screams]

171
00:12:57,819 --> 00:12:59,856
[Sarah] Do you remember
how his jaw just hung there?

172
00:12:59,946 --> 00:13:01,482
[Anne laughs] l do.

173
00:13:04,575 --> 00:13:06,657
-[Sarah] You must try to sleep.
-[Anne moans]

174
00:13:10,039 --> 00:13:11,120
[Sarah] You may go.

175
00:13:11,791 --> 00:13:13,077
-[Anne] Don't leave me!
-[Sarah] I won't.

176
00:13:19,215 --> 00:13:20,546
- Are you still there?
- Yes.

177
00:13:29,809 --> 00:13:31,015
- Are you still there?
- Yes.

178
00:14:00,673 --> 00:14:02,630
[muffled chatter]

179
00:14:15,355 --> 00:14:18,188
[Abigail] For the queen.
The doctor's ordered it immediately.

180
00:14:18,274 --> 00:14:19,890
It's a matter of extreme urgency.

181
00:14:19,984 --> 00:14:21,065
She's sleeping.

182
00:14:23,363 --> 00:14:25,354
Shall I tell the doctor
you imperiled the queen's health

183
00:14:25,448 --> 00:14:27,234
and let you rue the ramifications?

184
00:14:28,534 --> 00:14:30,741
What does "ramific..."

185
00:14:31,162 --> 00:14:32,869
It means he will have you whipped.

186
00:15:08,574 --> 00:15:10,281
[door opens]

187
00:15:10,535 --> 00:15:11,525
What are you doing?

188
00:15:12,161 --> 00:15:14,243
[Abigail] This is peleatis, the herb.

189
00:15:14,956 --> 00:15:16,196
I out some this morning.

190
00:15:16,541 --> 00:15:19,249
It reduces swelling and inflammation.
I thought it may help the queen.

191
00:15:19,335 --> 00:15:20,791
You cannot just walk in here.

192
00:15:21,546 --> 00:15:23,253
Why did the footman let you through?

193
00:15:24,882 --> 00:15:26,668
It's not his fault. I lied to him.

194
00:15:26,759 --> 00:15:28,295
[footman] The prime minister
and Mr. Marlborough.

195
00:15:28,386 --> 00:15:31,003
L just wanted to help her.
She seemed to suffer so much.

196
00:15:31,389 --> 00:15:32,220
Footman.

197
00:15:32,765 --> 00:15:33,800
Take her downstairs.

198
00:15:34,225 --> 00:15:37,138
Tell Mrs. Meg she is to receive
six of the birch. Go.

199
00:15:38,563 --> 00:15:40,395
It's peleatis, the herb.

200
00:15:46,195 --> 00:15:48,937
Anne, you must focus.

201
00:15:49,866 --> 00:15:53,905
[Marlborough] We gather our forces here.
The Austrians mass here.

202
00:15:54,745 --> 00:15:56,327
[Anne] Which country is that again?

203
00:15:56,414 --> 00:15:57,996
[Sarah] Listen. Marlborough.

204
00:15:58,499 --> 00:15:59,864
[Marlborough] This is the town of Lille,

205
00:16:00,585 --> 00:16:03,327
in a valley in France.

206
00:16:03,713 --> 00:16:06,831
We lure them in by sending a small force
to engage them.

207
00:16:06,924 --> 00:16:08,085
They give chase.

208
00:16:08,176 --> 00:16:10,508
We descend in numbers from above.

209
00:16:10,595 --> 00:16:13,178
-[all] Hear, hear!
- Hear, hear! It is an excellent plan.

210
00:16:13,264 --> 00:16:14,595
Queen Anne, do you agree?

211
00:16:15,266 --> 00:16:17,177
The people expect it to be over.

212
00:16:17,518 --> 00:16:20,886
Well, we all want it to be over,
but wishing does not make it so.

213
00:16:21,397 --> 00:16:24,139
We could sue for peace,
but we will not get it.

214
00:16:25,151 --> 00:16:26,141
It does help.

215
00:16:28,905 --> 00:16:29,815
What?

216
00:16:29,906 --> 00:16:33,149
There's something soothing on my legs,
it takes the burn out. What is it?

217
00:16:33,367 --> 00:16:35,199
Oh, herbs, of some sort.

218
00:16:40,875 --> 00:16:42,661
[Abigail] Please, please.

219
00:16:45,796 --> 00:16:46,706
What is going on?

220
00:16:46,797 --> 00:16:49,380
Do her in the barn, if that's what it is,
not in my kitchen.

221
00:16:49,467 --> 00:16:51,799
Her Ladyship says six of the birch
for this one.

222
00:16:51,886 --> 00:16:53,092
[Abigail whimpers]

223
00:17:01,562 --> 00:17:03,599
[screams]

224
00:17:05,191 --> 00:17:06,022
[Cries]

225
00:17:06,943 --> 00:17:07,808
[Sarah] Stop.

226
00:17:08,778 --> 00:17:09,768
Let her go.

227
00:17:10,488 --> 00:17:11,523
Come with me.

228
00:17:12,490 --> 00:17:14,606
[Abigail panting]

229
00:17:18,037 --> 00:17:20,324
So, you are perhaps too kind
for your own good.

230
00:17:21,541 --> 00:17:22,827
It has been said.

231
00:17:23,584 --> 00:17:24,870
Which leads to stupidity.

232
00:17:27,505 --> 00:17:29,746
The queen is soothed somewhat,
so I thank you.

233
00:17:30,258 --> 00:17:32,124
You will get me some more of those herbs

234
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:34,091
and not overstep again.

235
00:17:36,597 --> 00:17:38,383
My father always spoke highly of you.

236
00:17:40,059 --> 00:17:41,174
I liked your father.

237
00:17:41,769 --> 00:17:43,180
He had charm to burn.

238
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:45,470
Then I guess he did.

239
00:17:48,609 --> 00:17:49,849
You have fallen far.

240
00:17:51,988 --> 00:17:54,320
When I was 15,
my father lost me in a card game.

241
00:17:55,116 --> 00:17:56,481
You are not serious.

242
00:17:57,827 --> 00:17:58,817
This one here.

243
00:17:59,412 --> 00:18:01,119
[Abigail] He was very upset about it.

244
00:18:01,998 --> 00:18:03,033
Took off into the forest

245
00:18:03,124 --> 00:18:06,242
with nothing but a scullery maid
and a dozen bottles for solace.

246
00:18:06,335 --> 00:18:07,416
[Sarah] And you went?

247
00:18:08,004 --> 00:18:09,870
[Abigail] I wanted to do right
by my father.

248
00:18:10,506 --> 00:18:13,874
The debt was to a balloon-shaped
German man with a thin cock.

249
00:18:14,969 --> 00:18:18,553
Thankfully, I managed to convince him a
woman has her blood in 28 days a month.

250
00:18:19,557 --> 00:18:21,389
[chuckles quietly]

251
00:18:23,561 --> 00:18:24,801
What happened to your hand?

252
00:18:26,522 --> 00:18:30,186
[Abigail] Some of my...
colleagues are immune to my charms.

253
00:18:36,490 --> 00:18:38,447
[classical music playing]

254
00:18:44,498 --> 00:18:46,535
Earl Stratford,
do not come near me whining today

255
00:18:46,626 --> 00:18:48,583
or I will crush your tiny heart to liver.

256
00:18:49,837 --> 00:18:53,671
Madame Tournee. You may have
the tapestry budget you asked for.

257
00:18:53,758 --> 00:18:56,591
Spend one penny more
and I will take your fingernails in lieu.

258
00:18:57,053 --> 00:18:58,043
[Tournee] Merci.

259
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:04,015
Abigail, get a platter of oysters
sent to the Dutch ambassador.

260
00:19:04,101 --> 00:19:05,182
Yes, Your Ladyship.

261
00:19:05,811 --> 00:19:06,972
[Sarah] Colonel Masham.

262
