00:37:24,033 --> 00:37:24,864
Abigail.

514
00:37:25,577 --> 00:37:26,408
[gasps]

515
00:37:28,580 --> 00:37:30,366
If you forget to load the pellet,

516
00:37:30,457 --> 00:37:33,040
the gun fires, makes the sound,
but releases no shot.

517
00:37:34,127 --> 00:37:35,788
It is a great jape. Do you agree?

518
00:37:36,629 --> 00:37:37,460
Yes.

519
00:37:38,047 --> 00:37:41,256
Maybe we will think of
a use for it one day.

520
00:37:41,676 --> 00:37:44,919
Sometimes, it is hard to remember
whether you have loaded the pellet or not.

521
00:37:45,221 --> 00:37:48,589
I do fear confusion and accidents.

522
00:37:49,100 --> 00:37:50,682
I'm sure people will be careful.

523
00:38:27,096 --> 00:38:27,927
[gagging]

524
00:38:42,612 --> 00:38:44,523
[breathes deeply]

525
00:39:09,806 --> 00:39:12,343
[Sarah] Beef, 12 guineas.

526
00:39:12,809 --> 00:39:13,844
Cream.

527
00:39:14,227 --> 00:39:15,809
Mrs. Meg, your cream bill is outrageous.

528
00:39:15,895 --> 00:39:17,602
Are you bathing in it
to help your hemorrhoids?

529
00:39:17,689 --> 00:39:19,350
No, Your Ladyship.

530
00:39:19,440 --> 00:39:20,680
[Harley] May I examine?

531
00:39:20,775 --> 00:39:21,606
Of course.

532
00:39:23,820 --> 00:39:25,982
It's perfect, Lady Marlborough, as always.

533
00:39:27,323 --> 00:39:30,156
[page whispering]
The queen. It is rather urgent.

534
00:39:31,911 --> 00:39:32,992
Shall we sign off?

535
00:39:33,705 --> 00:39:34,536
Of course.

536
00:39:37,625 --> 00:39:38,956
[classical music playing]

537
00:40:00,481 --> 00:40:01,846
Aim for the flagstones.

538
00:40:01,941 --> 00:40:03,352
The lawn might break your fall.

539
00:40:03,818 --> 00:40:05,149
[Anne] You do not care.

540
00:40:05,236 --> 00:40:06,647
Mrs. Morley.

541
00:40:07,280 --> 00:40:08,520
- Please!
- No!

542
00:40:09,115 --> 00:40:11,277
[Cries]

543
00:40:13,286 --> 00:40:14,526
[music fades]

544
00:40:15,121 --> 00:40:16,236
[Anne] Stay a while.

545
00:40:16,831 --> 00:40:18,788
No! Take the day off. I command it.

546
00:40:18,875 --> 00:40:20,286
Someone must run things.

547
00:40:20,919 --> 00:40:22,125
I am not food.

548
00:40:22,378 --> 00:40:23,709
You cannot just eat and eat.

549
00:40:23,796 --> 00:40:25,958
[Anne] Yet you are tasty and salty.

550
00:40:27,550 --> 00:40:30,417
[squeals] If I grilled you,
you'd make a delightful meal.

551
00:40:31,095 --> 00:40:32,085
Very well.

552
00:40:32,180 --> 00:40:35,138
I will come and see you this afternoon,
and we can play whist.

553
00:40:35,934 --> 00:40:37,720
[footsteps]

554
00:40:41,606 --> 00:40:43,017
[classical music playing]

555
00:40:46,527 --> 00:40:50,236
[Godolphin] The opposition asks us

556
00:40:50,323 --> 00:40:52,735
-to be halfhearted in this war!
-[loud, indistinct chatter]

557
00:40:53,618 --> 00:40:55,734
- We will not!
-[man] Hear, hear!

558
00:40:58,998 --> 00:41:00,989
We must wear our griefs,

559
00:41:01,334 --> 00:41:04,076
for England is worth our all,

560
00:41:04,629 --> 00:41:06,745
and suffer we must for her!

561
00:41:07,507 --> 00:41:08,713
Mr. Harley,

562
00:41:09,092 --> 00:41:10,958
control your rabble!

563
00:41:12,345 --> 00:41:15,679
I am, therefore, announcing today

564
00:41:15,765 --> 00:41:17,631
-that, at Her Majesty's...
-[music fades]

565
00:41:18,768 --> 00:41:21,305
About time, Mrs. Freeman.
This fucking leg.

566
00:41:21,980 --> 00:41:23,721
It's like a monster attacking me.

567
00:41:24,148 --> 00:41:25,354
Cut it off for me, will you?

568
00:41:25,441 --> 00:41:26,977
[Abigail] I don't think so, Your Majesty.

569
00:41:29,821 --> 00:41:30,731
Why are you here?

570
00:41:33,241 --> 00:41:35,824
Lady Marlborough sent me,
as I am an excellent whist player

571
00:41:35,910 --> 00:41:38,618
and she has been unavoidably detained
with business of state,

572
00:41:38,705 --> 00:41:39,911
but will be here posthaste.

573
00:41:39,998 --> 00:41:41,079
It's my state.

574
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:44,537
I am the business of state.
Did she actually send me her maid?

575
00:41:45,294 --> 00:41:46,910
[Abigail] Your Majesty,
I wasn't always a maid.

576
00:41:47,130 --> 00:41:49,121
I'm educated, I speak Latin, French.

577
00:41:49,716 --> 00:41:51,206
My family fell on hard times.

578
00:41:51,551 --> 00:41:53,258
- I'm also her cousin.
-lt's all very fascinating.

579
00:41:53,761 --> 00:41:55,798
You shall leave, regardless,
and tell her to come.

580
00:41:58,224 --> 00:41:59,134
They're gorgeous.

581
00:42:01,269 --> 00:42:03,180
They're my babies. Let them out, please.

582
00:42:08,443 --> 00:42:09,524
[Abigail] How many are there?

583
00:42:09,986 --> 00:42:11,101
[Anne] Seventeen.

584
00:42:12,530 --> 00:42:13,895
It's Hildebrand's day today.

585
00:42:16,117 --> 00:42:17,107
[Abigail] Which one is he?

586
00:42:17,910 --> 00:42:20,277
That one there. Shy, but stubborn.

587
00:42:21,831 --> 00:42:22,662
[Abigail] May I?

588
00:42:28,671 --> 00:42:29,661
[Anne] He likes you.

589
00:42:32,842 --> 00:42:34,833
I lost some 17 children.

590
00:42:40,266 --> 00:42:41,597
Some were born as blood,

591
00:42:42,310 --> 00:42:43,391
some without breath...

592
00:42:44,854 --> 00:42:46,845
and some were with me
for a very brief time.

593
00:42:52,403 --> 00:42:53,393
Oh, my dear.

594
00:42:57,408 --> 00:42:58,773
Today is Hildebrand's day.

595
00:42:59,952 --> 00:43:00,987
The day you lost him.

596
00:43:02,538 --> 00:43:03,369
Yes.

597
00:43:04,123 --> 00:43:06,660
Each one that dies,
a little bit of you goes with them.

598
00:43:11,422 --> 00:43:12,537
Would you like to join me?

599
00:43:17,011 --> 00:43:18,251
[Anne] Oh. Lovely cake.

600
00:43:19,680 --> 00:43:20,511
Yum.

601
00:43:21,432 --> 00:43:22,422
[Abigail] You like it?

602
00:43:24,685 --> 00:43:26,972
-[Anne] Delish.
-[Abigail] You do like it.

603
00:43:27,063 --> 00:43:28,224
[Anne] Hello, Sussy.

604
00:43:29,065 --> 00:43:30,931
Happy birthday.

605
00:43:31,692 --> 00:43:33,353
Come on. There's some for you, too.

606
00:43:33,444 --> 00:43:34,525
Don't eat Mummy's foot.

607
00:43:36,656 --> 00:43:37,487
[knocking on door]

608
00:43:43,913 --> 00:43:45,028
What an outfit.

609
00:43:46,374 --> 00:43:47,364
Thank you.

610
00:43:48,793 --> 00:43:50,283
I thought it might be too much.

611
00:43:50,878 --> 00:43:52,869
Have you come to seduce me or rape me?

612
00:43:54,090 --> 00:43:55,330
[Masham] I am a gentleman.

613
00:43:55,967 --> 00:43:56,957
So rape, then.

614
00:43:57,844 --> 00:43:58,754
[Masham] No.

615
00:43:58,845 --> 00:44:00,961
No, you are...

616
00:44:02,056 --> 00:44:04,388
You have intrigued me.

617
00:44:06,686 --> 00:44:07,676
And you, me.

618
00:44:09,355 --> 00:44:11,813
I'm intrigued by what you look like
under all this.

619
00:44:30,126 --> 00:44:31,116
You're handsome.

620
00:44:32,336 --> 00:44:33,792
No wonder you cover it up.

621
00:44:34,088 --> 00:44:35,078
Who are you?

622
00:44:35,590 --> 00:44:36,876
No ordinary maid.

623
00:44:36,966 --> 00:44:38,832
It could be said I have fallen far.

624
00:44:40,011 --> 00:44:42,844
It could be said I aim to catch you.

625
00:44:46,934 --> 00:44:47,765
[Masham] Ow!

626
00:44:48,269 --> 00:44:49,259
I might allow it.

627
00:44:50,771 --> 00:44:52,182
Now good night, sir.

628
00:44:57,570 --> 00:44:58,401
Progress?

629
00:44:59,322 --> 00:45:00,858
Uh... She, uh...

630
00:45:01,949 --> 00:45:03,405
- She bit me.
- Oh.

631
00:45:04,744 --> 00:45:06,075
This wig's ridiculous.

632
00:45:07,371 --> 00:45:08,657
A man must look pretty.

633
00:45:09,290 --> 00:45:10,997
I'm not entirely sure she approves.

634
00:45:12,168 --> 00:45:14,079
Try again in your own way, old boy.

635
00:45:14,503 --> 00:45:15,618
[classical music playing]

636
00:45:42,740 --> 00:45:44,481
[music continues]

637
00:46:07,598 --> 00:46:09,180
[music fades]

638
00:46:10,685 --> 00:46:12,972
[Sarah] Apologies regarding
sending Abigail in my stead.

639
00:46:13,062 --> 00:46:14,348
[Anne] She was perfectly darling.

640
00:46:14,438 --> 00:46:15,974
Hildebrand really took to her.

641
00:46:16,065 --> 00:46:17,146
Is that a rabbit?

642
00:46:19,568 --> 00:46:21,309
Anne, you are too sensitive.

643
00:46:21,821 --> 00:46:24,188
And you are too mean and uncaring,
some days.

644
00:46:24,282 --> 00:46:27,445
Some days, I'm quite lovely, though.
Let's think on them.

645
00:46:28,828 --> 00:46:29,659
[Sarah] Anne.

646
00:46:31,080 --> 00:46:32,411
You're such a child.

647
00:46:48,764 --> 00:46:50,926
[Abigail] I guess all the rapes
were the hardest.

648
00:46:52,643 --> 00:46:54,054
Made me feel at their mercy.

649
00:46:55,229 --> 00:46:56,219
That I was nothing.

650
00:46:57,189 --> 00:47:00,022
You are not nothing. You're a dear person.

651
00:47:00,109 --> 00:47:01,099
Thank you.

652
00:47:03,237 --> 00:47:04,398
You're so beautiful.

653
00:47:05,197 --> 00:47:06,813
Stop it. You mock me.

654
00:47:07,408 --> 00:47:08,398
I do not.

655
00:47:09,285 --> 00:47:12,027
If I were a man, I would ravish you.

656
00:47:12,955 --> 00:47:13,990
- Ravish.
- Enough.

657
00:47:14,582 --> 00:47:16,539
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

658
00:47:16,625 --> 00:47:18,241
[music playing, distant]

659
00:47:18,336 --> 00:47:19,371
Oh, look.

660
00:47:23,758 --> 00:47:25,715
[children playing music]

661
00:47:45,988 --> 00:47:46,944
Make them stop.

662
00:47:47,698 --> 00:47:48,733
What?

663
00:47:48,824 --> 00:47:49,655
Stop!

664
00:47:50,910 --> 00:47:51,820
Enough!

665
00:47:51,911 --> 00:47:52,821
Stop!

666
00:47:53,579 --> 00:47:54,740
Be gone!

667
00:47:54,830 --> 00:47:56,446
I command it!

668
00:47:57,208 --> 00:47:58,289
Leave!

669
00:47:59,627 --> 00:48:01,493
I don't want to hear it!

670
00:48:04,256 --> 00:48:05,997
-[Abigail] Your Majesty?
- Now I must rest.

671
00:48:06,092 --> 00:48:07,332
- Shall I...
- Leave me be!

672
00:48:07,426 --> 00:48:09,417
[classical music playing]

673
00:48:34,954 --> 00:48:36,945
[music continues]

674
00:48:40,626 --> 00:48:41,616
Give me that.

675
00:48:43,087 --> 00:48:44,077
Give me that.

676
00:48:44,171 --> 00:48:46,208
{baby coos]
-[Anne laughing]

677
00:48:48,217 --> 00:48:50,083
Thank you, Your Majesty.

678
00:48:51,929 --> 00:48:53,590
[baby cries]

679
00:49:01,188 --> 00:49:02,303
Where am I?

680
00:49:04,483 --> 00:49:05,939
Where am I?

681
00:49:06,026 --> 00:49:08,893
[page] Your Majesty,
you are in the west hallway.

682
00:49:09,655 --> 00:49:11,237
Don't speak to me like that!

683
00:49:12,533 --> 00:49:13,773
[Cries]

684
00:49:13,868 --> 00:49:14,858
[Abigail] Your Majesty.

685
00:49:15,870 --> 00:49:18,453
- Stupid girl! Where have you been?
-[Abigail] I'm sorry.

686
00:49:22,418 --> 00:49:23,408
[Anne] Take me back.

687
00:49:25,004 --> 00:49:26,995
[music continues]

688
00:49:37,141 --> 00:49:38,176
[sobs]

689
00:50:03,292 --> 00:50:04,282
[music fades]

690
00:50:04,376 --> 00:50:05,582
[Abigail] Perhaps we should dance.

691
00:50:08,130 --> 00:50:09,336
You mock me.

692
00:50:09,423 --> 00:50:10,788
[Abigail] No. I just believe you can.

693
00:50:11,550 --> 00:50:12,665
That it would be cheery.

694
00:50:13,886 --> 00:50:15,547
I would dearly like to dance with you.

695
00:50:17,973 --> 00:50:19,964
[pigeons cooing]

696
00:50:24,271 --> 00:50:25,102
[both] Back.

697
00:50:28,025 --> 00:50:29,561
Together. And click.

698
00:50:32,112 --> 00:50:33,102
[gun cocking]

699
00:50:33,197 --> 00:50:35,234
-[Sarah] Throw.
-[wings flapping]

700
00:50:35,324 --> 00:50:37,986
- [gunshot]
- Back, front, back.

701
00:50:38,869 --> 00:50:40,030
[gun cocks]

702
00:50:40,120 --> 00:50:40,951
[Sarah] Throw.

703
00:50:41,330 --> 00:50:42,161
[[gunshot]

704
00:50:42,540 --> 00:50:45,373
Off with her head and off with her head.

705
00:50:45,459 --> 00:50:46,369
[both laugh]

706
00:50:46,460 --> 00:50:48,918
[pigeons cooing]

707
00:50:49,838 --> 00:50:50,669
-[gun cocks]
-[Sarah] Throw.

708
00:50:50,756 --> 00:50:52,417
[Abigail] Spin, spin, spin, spin.

709
00:50:52,508 --> 00:50:53,339
[Anne laughs]

710
00:50:53,968 --> 00:50:55,049
[gunshot]

711
00:50:55,970 --> 00:50:58,086
[wings flapping]

712
00:51:00,516 --> 00:51:02,848
-[gun cocks]
-[wings flapping]

713
00:51:02,935 --> 00:51:03,925
[gunshot]

714
00:51:08,023 --> 00:51:09,013
[Sarah] It's 12-11.

715
00:51:09,942 --> 00:51:12,058
You're shooting
exceptionally well, Abigail.

716
00:51:12,152 --> 00:51:13,313
[Abigail] You've taught me well.

717
00:51:14,863 --> 00:51:18,026
I hope you haven't found your time
with the queen too tedious.

718
00:51:18,117 --> 00:51:21,075
Oh, not at all.
And if it gives you rest, I'm happy.

719
00:51:22,121 --> 00:51:24,328
- Did you sleep well?
- Like a shot badger.

720
00:51:24,415 --> 00:51:25,246
Excellent.

721
00:51:26,125 --> 00:51:27,115
The queen is...

722
00:51:29,336 --> 00:51:30,701
an extraordinary person...

723
00:51:31,755 --> 00:51:33,462
even if it's not readily apparent.

724
00:51:34,383 --> 00:51:36,044
She's been stalked by tragedy.

725
00:51:36,135 --> 00:51:37,421
She seems quite lovely.

726
00:51:38,387 --> 00:51:39,798
[Sarah] I will not burden you again.

727
00:51:41,181 --> 00:51:42,842
- I'm quite happy to...
- I know you are.

728
00:51:43,642 --> 00:51:45,679
She will be angry if I do not appear soon.

729
00:51:47,187 --> 00:51:48,222
Take your shot.

730
00:51:57,865 --> 00:51:58,730
Throw.

731
00:52:03,829 --> 00:52:04,660
[Abigail] Thirteen.

732
00:52:12,254 --> 00:52:13,244
[Sarah] The queen?

733
00:52:13,797 --> 00:52:14,912
I will be there directly.

734
00:52:20,095 --> 00:52:22,553
The queen... asked for her.

735
00:52:29,772 --> 00:52:32,560
I have sent for some lobsters. I thought
we could race them and then eat them.

736
00:52:32,650 --> 00:52:34,311
- Oh, hello.
- Oh, hello.

737
00:52:34,860 --> 00:52:36,442
I hope you have three.

738
00:52:36,528 --> 00:52:39,236
You sent for Abigail
to try and make me jealous, I think.

739
00:52:39,323 --> 00:52:40,154
Perhaps.

740
00:52:41,283 --> 00:52:42,489
[Anne gasps]

741
00:52:42,826 --> 00:52:44,237
They'll be in with the lobsters.

742
00:52:44,662 --> 00:52:45,572
You scared?

743
00:52:45,663 --> 00:52:46,824
[door opens]

744
00:52:46,914 --> 00:52:50,782
Oh, I think a moat is a bad idea.
It's just-- It's too old-fashioned.

745
00:52:52,127 --> 00:52:54,334
Your lobsters, ma'am.
Where should I put them?

746
00:52:54,421 --> 00:52:56,128
Uh... here.

747
00:53:08,018 --> 00:53:09,053
[exclaims]

748
00:53:10,104 --> 00:53:12,311
Hello. Remember me?

749
00:53:13,232 --> 00:53:14,222
[Abigail] Mr. Harley.

750
00:53:15,025 --> 00:53:16,561
You always unbalance me.

751
00:53:17,194 --> 00:53:18,355
[Harley] So what's been happening?

752
00:53:19,947 --> 00:53:22,939
The queen and Lady Marlborough
are to race lobsters and then eat them.

753
00:53:23,033 --> 00:53:24,364
Do you want to get punched?

754
00:53:25,452 --> 00:53:26,658
The queen is going to announce

755
00:53:26,745 --> 00:53:28,452
the doubling of the landholders' tax
to parliament.

756
00:53:28,539 --> 00:53:29,779
Do you jest?

757
00:53:29,873 --> 00:53:31,739
I don't think she's certain of it, though.

758
00:53:31,834 --> 00:53:33,916
But Lady Marlborough
is providing that certainty.

759
00:53:34,002 --> 00:53:34,833
Yes.

760
00:53:35,671 --> 00:53:36,502
And?

761
00:53:37,131 --> 00:53:38,121
That is all.

762
00:53:39,550 --> 00:53:41,166
Why do I feel that is not all?

763
00:53:43,512 --> 00:53:45,253
I'm trying my best.

764
00:53:46,348 --> 00:53:47,179
I am.

765
00:53:48,559 --> 00:53:51,802
All right, turn off the tears. Thank you.
Have a pleasant evening.

766
00:54:01,113 --> 00:54:03,730
May I speak a moment,
with Her Majesty's pleasure?

767
00:54:06,910 --> 00:54:10,744
May I exhort the chamber
to roar a mighty hurrah for Her Majesty

768
00:54:10,831 --> 00:54:13,698
in her brilliant decision
to not raise the land tax.

769
00:54:14,251 --> 00:54:16,333
-[crowd] Hurrah!
-[Harley] For the doubling

770
00:54:16,420 --> 00:54:19,754
of the tax would have been a disaster,
and the fields would have run with blood

771
00:54:19,840 --> 00:54:22,582
as the countryside rose up
against our city friends,

772
00:54:22,676 --> 00:54:26,840
to add to the piling dead of our sons
already on the field of this war.

773
00:54:27,389 --> 00:54:29,926
Again, to our queen, for her deep wisdom

774
00:54:30,309 --> 00:54:33,176
in knowing where to draw the line
in holding our country together.

775
00:54:33,604 --> 00:54:36,187
For there is no point winning a war abroad

776
00:54:36,273 --> 00:54:37,934
if we are to star': one at home.

777
00:54:38,025 --> 00:54:39,641
-[crowd] Hear, hear!
-[crowd] Hurrah!

778
00:54:39,735 --> 00:54:41,692
[Harley] I apologize for the interruption,
Your Majesty.

779
00:54:42,112 --> 00:54:43,523
The floor is yours, of course.

780
00:54:44,072 --> 00:54:46,154
We look forward to hearing
what you have to say.

781
00:55:03,383 --> 00:55:05,374
[indistinct chatter]

782
00:55:16,313 --> 00:55:18,145
[imitation animal sound]

783
00:55:20,025 --> 00:55:21,811
[clicking]

784
00:55:28,158 --> 00:55:30,616
-[screams]
-[screams]

785
00:55:33,121 --> 00:55:34,907
[Abigail] Men should not
sneak up on women.

786
00:55:34,998 --> 00:55:36,238
You look scared.

787
00:55:36,333 --> 00:55:37,323
[Masham] I'm hurt.

788
00:55:39,628 --> 00:55:40,709
[Abigail shrieks]

789
00:55:51,056 --> 00:55:53,423
-[Masham grunts]
-[Abigail shrieks]

790
00:55:56,562 --> 00:55:57,893
[Abigail] Wait, wait!

791
00:55:59,231 --> 00:56:00,392
Kiss me properly first.

792
00:56:02,234 --> 00:56:03,690
-[Masham grunts]
-[Abigail giggles]

793
00:56:12,744 --> 00:56:14,906
I have just now decided
to marry you, Masham.

794
00:56:14,997 --> 00:56:16,783
I cannot marry a servant.

795
00:56:16,874 --> 00:56:18,035
I can enjoy one, though.

796
00:56:23,171 --> 00:56:24,957
I know it would ruin you to marry me.

797
00:56:25,048 --> 00:56:26,254
I will fix things for us.

798
00:56:36,059 --> 00:56:37,675
Don't you think we are a good match?

799
00:56:38,312 --> 00:56:39,677
I think a very good match.

800
00:56:41,315 --> 00:56:42,146
[Masham screams]

801
00:57:35,744 --> 00:57:37,405
I looked like a fool.

802
00:57:37,496 --> 00:57:38,827
They were all staring, weren't they?

803
00:57:38,914 --> 00:57:41,872
I can tell even if I can't see,
and I heard the word "fat." Fat.

804
00:57:41,959 --> 00:57:43,074
- And ugly.
- Anne.

805
00:57:43,669 --> 00:57:45,706
No one but me would dare, and I did not.

806
00:57:46,296 --> 00:57:48,913
I felt for you. He set you up.
It is our fault.

807
00:57:49,007 --> 00:57:51,419
I didn't know what else to do.
I couldn't go through with it.

808
00:57:51,510 --> 00:57:53,922
It's fine, Anne. It's fine.

809
00:58:00,978 --> 00:58:02,468
He was ready for us.

810
00:58:02,562 --> 00:58:05,554
He probably just assumed
that you've been working on her.

811
00:58:05,983 --> 00:58:07,018
A minor hitch.

812
00:58:07,526 --> 00:58:08,937
We will reset the date.

813
00:58:22,249 --> 00:58:23,410
[Anne] What are you doing?

814
00:58:25,544 --> 00:58:26,625
Oh, Your Majesty.

815
00:58:28,714 --> 00:58:31,251
Lady Marlborough asked me to wait for you,
and I was...

816
00:58:32,676 --> 00:58:35,088
The bed looked so beautiful,
and I was overcome...

817
00:58:36,096 --> 00:58:37,586
with foolishness. I'm sorry.

818
00:58:41,268 --> 00:58:42,554
Well, you may get out now.

819
00:58:57,325 --> 00:58:59,282
Apologies again, Your Majesty.

820
00:58:59,911 --> 00:59:01,072
What happened to your dress?

821
00:59:03,248 --> 00:59:04,238
Wolves.

822
00:59:30,734 --> 00:59:31,724
Her legs.

823
00:59:46,083 --> 00:59:47,073
[Anne] Rub my legs.

824
01:00:11,608 --> 01:00:12,894
[Abigail] Does it hurt a lot?

825
01:00:14,402 --> 01:00:15,392
They're agony.

826
01:00:52,232 --> 01:00:54,018
[moans pleasurably]

827
01:00:54,401 --> 01:00:55,562
Oh, the pain.

828
01:01:00,407 --> 01:01:01,818
Marlborough has written.

829
01:01:01,908 --> 01:01:02,898
He's in position.

830
01:01:03,785 --> 01:01:05,401
The battle will begin any time.

831
01:01:09,249 --> 01:01:10,910
He will prevail.

832
01:01:11,001 --> 01:01:12,082
Of course.

833
01:01:12,669 --> 01:01:16,003
I imagine you will not sleep tonight.
I can stay and sit with you.

834
01:01:16,089 --> 01:01:17,250
I'm all right.

835
01:03:02,445 --> 01:03:03,856
Good morning, Lady Marlborough.

836
01:03:04,698 --> 01:03:07,235
[Sarah] Did you see that book of poetry
from the Dryden fellow?

837
01:03:07,325 --> 01:03:09,066
I... have not.

838
01:03:09,160 --> 01:03:09,991
[Sarah] No.

839
01:03:10,495 --> 01:03:11,326
No.

840
01:03:12,163 --> 01:03:13,073
No.

841
01:03:14,291 --> 01:03:15,122
No.

842
01:03:15,959 --> 01:03:16,869
No.

843
01:03:18,545 --> 01:03:19,501
I don't understand.

844
01:03:19,587 --> 01:03:21,669
Did you take it? My book.

845
01:03:21,756 --> 01:03:22,712
[Abigail] No.

846
01:03:22,799 --> 01:03:25,461
I think you are a pretty little liar
that I have misjudged.

847
01:03:26,386 --> 01:03:28,047
I did not mean for this to happen.

848
01:03:29,014 --> 01:03:30,425
The queen, she's forceful.

849
01:03:30,515 --> 01:03:32,176
[Sarah] You are dismissed from my service.

850
01:03:32,976 --> 01:03:35,343
Go back to Mrs. Meg and tell her
to find you a position in the scullery.

851
01:03:35,437 --> 01:03:38,350
And if she asks why, tell her
â€œBecause I am a disloyal little bitch."

852
01:03:38,690 --> 01:03:40,055
Yes, Your Ladyship.

853
01:03:40,859 --> 01:03:42,270
It has been an honor and privilege--

854
01:03:42,360 --> 01:03:46,194
If you do not go, I will start kicking you
and I will not stop.

855
01:04:29,949 --> 01:04:31,906
[panting]

856
01:04:33,453 --> 01:04:34,659
[muffled crying]

857
01:04:51,721 --> 01:04:53,507
[crying continues]

858
01:05:06,152 --> 01:05:08,234
[sniffling]

859
01:05:10,698 --> 01:05:12,234
You have become close to Abigail.

860
01:05:12,325 --> 01:05:13,315
She's been a dear. Yes.

861
01:05:13,410 --> 01:05:16,277
It is such a shame,
but I've had to dismiss her for theft.

862
01:05:16,371 --> 01:05:17,953
She's a liar and a thief.

863
01:05:25,547 --> 01:05:27,788
Your tongue
seems uncharacteristically still.

864
01:05:27,882 --> 01:05:29,043
I heard you.

865
01:05:29,134 --> 01:05:31,000
She's my servant. She's not dismissed.

866
01:05:31,094 --> 01:05:32,505
I've made her my maid of the bedchamber.

867
01:05:32,595 --> 01:05:34,131
Did you not hear what I said?

868
01:05:34,222 --> 01:05:35,963
Yes, you regard her as a liar and a thief.

869
01:05:36,057 --> 01:05:38,219
- Yes.
- I do not, obviously.

870
01:05:40,812 --> 01:05:42,268
You will dismiss her.

871
01:05:42,355 --> 01:05:43,891
I don't want to.

872
01:05:43,982 --> 01:05:46,314
I like it when she puts her tongue
inside me.

873
01:05:46,901 --> 01:05:48,892
[classical music playing]

874
01:06:30,570 --> 01:06:32,561
[music fades]

875
01:06:40,580 --> 01:06:42,662
It feels so strange to be in this.

876
01:06:42,749 --> 01:06:43,955
It's good for you.

877
01:06:44,042 --> 01:06:46,033
The doctor says it'll leach the toxins.

878
01:06:47,003 --> 01:06:49,085
What if I should fall asleep
and slip under?

879
01:06:49,839 --> 01:06:51,375
Just imagine it's hot chocolate.

880
01:06:52,008 --> 01:06:53,840
- Oh, then I shall die happy.
-[Abigail giggles]

881
01:06:55,803 --> 01:06:56,964
[door opens]

882
01:06:58,848 --> 01:07:00,213
[door closes]

883
01:07:03,603 --> 01:07:06,345
[Sarah] After you left, I thought,
â€œWhat a grand idea to take to the mud."

884
01:07:07,023 --> 01:07:09,811
To get whatever poisons
one carries with one out.

885
01:07:12,737 --> 01:07:13,852
[mud sloshing]

886
01:07:15,573 --> 01:07:17,439
[Sarah] Abigail, could you fetch me
some refreshment?

887
01:07:18,618 --> 01:07:20,609
I would like to, of course, but...

888
01:07:20,703 --> 01:07:23,411
I must be at the queen's side
and behest at all times.

889
01:07:23,498 --> 01:07:24,579
It is my role.

890
01:07:25,416 --> 01:07:26,656
Such loyalty.

891
01:07:27,043 --> 01:07:30,536
How delightful it is when one tries to
cultivate a new trait in one's character.

892
01:07:30,838 --> 01:07:32,499
- Do not scratch at her.
-[Sarah scoffs]

893
01:07:40,348 --> 01:07:41,838
Mr. Freeman.

894
01:07:46,020 --> 01:07:47,510
Mr. Morley.

895
01:07:48,106 --> 01:07:50,848
Oh, how handsome you are.

896
01:07:51,776 --> 01:07:54,017
[Anne] How handsome you are, Mr. Freeman.

897
01:07:54,571 --> 01:07:56,733
[Sarah] Oh... But I...

898
01:07:57,448 --> 01:07:59,189
I forgot my glasses.

899
01:07:59,284 --> 01:08:01,491
[Anne and Sarah laugh]

900
01:08:03,830 --> 01:08:05,821
[chuckles]

901
01:08:12,880 --> 01:08:15,212
You will be back in the street.

902
01:08:24,642 --> 01:08:26,098
[Sarah] Do you remember
when we were young,

903
01:08:26,185 --> 01:08:28,597
and we were not allowed out in the snow,

904
01:08:29,188 --> 01:08:31,145
and we opened all the windows
in the ballroom

905
01:08:31,232 --> 01:08:33,599
and sat there
as the snow flurries just wafted in?

906
01:08:33,693 --> 01:08:38,312
And when your governess came in, we were
making a snowman and our hands were blue.

907
01:08:38,406 --> 01:08:40,864
-[Anne] Oh, it was such fun.
-[Abigail] Sounds marvelous.

908
01:08:40,950 --> 01:08:42,532
[Sarah] So many things
we have done together.

909
01:08:42,619 --> 01:08:44,201
[Abigail] I do love ancient history.

910
01:08:45,580 --> 01:08:47,116
Sorry, Abigail, did you say something?

911
01:08:47,206 --> 01:08:50,073
Oh, I was singing.
I cannot get a tune out of my head.

912
01:08:50,168 --> 01:08:51,909
[Sarah] Well, there is
so much room for it.

913
01:08:52,003 --> 01:08:53,164
[Abigail chuckles]

914
01:08:53,504 --> 01:08:55,871
Lady Marlborough, you're such a wit.

915
01:08:55,965 --> 01:08:57,751
Oh, Abigail, you are a dear.

916
01:08:57,842 --> 01:08:59,958
I think I shall retire for the evening.

917
01:09:00,053 --> 01:09:01,885
Shall I prepare your bed, Queen Anne?

918
01:09:02,639 --> 01:09:06,007
Or shall you and I adjourn
to your apartments for some sherry?

919
01:09:06,100 --> 01:09:07,261
[Anne] Oh!

920
01:09:07,352 --> 01:09:09,343
Sherry sounds just the ticket.

921
01:09:09,437 --> 01:09:10,347
Good night, Abigail.

922
01:09:10,438 --> 01:09:12,600
Yes, good night, dear Abigail.

923
01:09:17,570 --> 01:09:20,813
You are enjoying all of this, aren't you?

924
01:09:20,907 --> 01:09:22,648
To be beloved? Of course.

925
01:09:22,742 --> 01:09:26,326
To see you trying to win me.
Why, what is not to love, my dear?

926
01:09:26,412 --> 01:09:31,452
You will stop this ridiculous infatuation.
You have made your point.

927
01:09:31,542 --> 01:09:33,624
Perhaps I was not making a point.

928
01:09:48,267 --> 01:09:50,178
[Abigail] Perhaps because of my past,

929
01:09:50,645 --> 01:09:52,852
perhaps a malformation of my heart.

930
01:09:53,815 --> 01:09:56,307
I blame my father, of course. Cunt.

931
01:09:57,777 --> 01:10:00,109
I must take control of my circumstance.

932
01:10:01,155 --> 01:10:03,897
I will need to act in a way
that meets with the edges of my morality.

933
01:10:06,119 --> 01:10:09,282
And when I end up on the street
selling my asshole to syphilitic soldiers,

934
01:10:09,372 --> 01:10:12,785
steadfast morality will be a
fucking nonsense that will mock me daily.

935
01:10:13,459 --> 01:10:14,290
I'm not quite following.

936
01:10:14,377 --> 01:10:15,208
Shh.

937
01:10:17,004 --> 01:10:18,961
I apologize.
But do "shh" when I'm thinking.

938
01:10:22,635 --> 01:10:24,217
Your hair is so lustrous.

939
01:10:25,346 --> 01:10:27,383
It's something people in court comment on.

940
01:10:27,473 --> 01:10:28,759
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

941
01:10:29,392 --> 01:10:31,383
I always thought of it
as rather nest-like.

942
01:10:31,477 --> 01:10:32,592
Not at all.

943
01:10:34,021 --> 01:10:35,261
[footman] Lady Marlborough.

944
01:10:35,356 --> 01:10:37,017
I shall make you tea.

945
01:10:37,400 --> 01:10:39,687
- What a lovely idea. Thank you, Abigail.
-[Abigail] Of course.

946
01:10:39,777 --> 01:10:41,267
[Anne] Pat the kids hello.

947
01:10:41,362 --> 01:10:42,352
Of course.

948
01:10:57,128 --> 01:10:59,916
You will give that speech on
the tax increase in parliament next week.

949
01:11:01,591 --> 01:11:04,253
[Anne] I dreamed of the man
on the roadside with one eye.

950
01:11:04,343 --> 01:11:05,253
[Sarah] What man?

951
01:11:05,970 --> 01:11:07,256
We drove through town.

952
01:11:07,930 --> 01:11:10,012
He looked at me in such a way,
it made my blood chill.

953
01:11:11,017 --> 01:11:12,132
So kind.

954
01:11:12,226 --> 01:11:14,012
[Anne] Abigail, do you think the people
are angry?

955
01:11:14,103 --> 01:11:16,219
Anne, she does not know.

956
01:11:16,314 --> 01:11:19,807
We should ask people. Get some people in
from the villages and ask them.

957
01:11:19,901 --> 01:11:21,983
[Sarah] That is not how matters of state
are dealt with.

958
01:11:22,069 --> 01:11:23,776
People are led. They do not lead.

959
01:11:24,447 --> 01:11:26,108
Would you leave Marlborough exposed?

960
01:11:26,199 --> 01:11:28,406
He needs another battalion
ready to join him, and that means money.

961
01:11:28,493 --> 01:11:29,949
Do not shout at me. I am the queen.

962
01:11:30,036 --> 01:11:31,572
Then for once act like one.

963
01:11:59,732 --> 01:12:01,723
[classical music playing]

964
01:12:06,364 --> 01:12:07,604
Is the queen not riding today?

965
01:12:08,032 --> 01:12:09,022
Do not speak to me.

966
01:12:29,053 --> 01:12:31,044
[music continues]

967
01:13:10,219 --> 01:13:11,050
[gags]

968
01:13:15,600 --> 01:13:17,591
[coughs]

969
01:13:41,250 --> 01:13:43,491
[music fades]

970
01:13:47,256 --> 01:13:50,089
[indistinct chatter, laughing]

971
01:13:57,183 --> 01:13:59,094
I have thought on the terms
of our friendship.

972
01:14:00,019 --> 01:14:01,760
I thought it was unconditional love.

973
01:14:01,854 --> 01:14:04,972
I will get you an audience with the queen
if you ask her a favor for me.

974
01:14:05,066 --> 01:14:07,808
- Wench. You--
- Harley, you do not need me as an enemy.

975
01:14:08,194 --> 01:14:10,435
As it turns out,
I am capable of much unpleasantness.

976
01:14:10,947 --> 01:14:11,857
As am I.

977
01:14:11,948 --> 01:14:14,406
[Abigail] You're so tiring,
being like this.

978
01:14:14,492 --> 01:14:16,358
The queen has taken a shine to me,

979
01:14:16,452 --> 01:14:19,319
and I will drip poison into her ear
regarding you

980
01:14:19,413 --> 01:14:21,324
until she is mad with hatred for you.

981
01:14:21,415 --> 01:14:24,373
Or we could have
a mutually advantageous friendship.

982
01:14:24,835 --> 01:14:26,075
Count of three. Yes or no?

983
01:14:26,921 --> 01:14:29,663
Well, if you're so close to the queen,
why not just ask this favor yourself?

984
01:14:29,757 --> 01:14:32,124
[Abigail] I do not want her to ever think
I want anything from her.

985
01:14:32,843 --> 01:14:34,584
- Have you counseled her for our side?
- No.

986
01:14:35,471 --> 01:14:37,428
[Harley] The country's future
hangs in the balance.

987
01:14:37,515 --> 01:14:39,176
Mm-hmm. My thing is what I wish
to talk about.

988
01:14:39,475 --> 01:14:40,385
You do not care?

989
01:14:40,893 --> 01:14:42,554
I thought you were on our side.

990
01:14:42,645 --> 01:14:44,056
[Abigail] I'm on my side.

991
01:14:44,438 --> 01:14:45,394
Always.

992
01:14:45,940 --> 01:14:47,806
Sometimes,
it's a happy coincidence for you.

993
01:14:48,609 --> 01:14:52,068
Like now.
You'll get a chance to save the country.

994
01:15:01,622 --> 01:15:03,329
[moaning]

995
01:15:07,044 --> 01:15:09,001
[grunting]

996
01:15:17,763 --> 01:15:19,549
[Harley] What tremendous luck
to find you in the garden.

997
01:15:20,057 --> 01:15:21,138
[Anne] We were taking the air.

998
01:15:21,642 --> 01:15:23,303
[Harley] You do not like the war,
I know that.

999
01:15:24,228 --> 01:15:27,346
[Anne] No, I do not,
but we must fight for what we fight for.

1000
01:15:28,107 --> 01:15:30,098
[Harley] Godolphin and Lady Marlborough
seem to have corralled you

1001
01:15:30,192 --> 01:15:32,308
so you do not get to hear
from your loyal opposition.

1002
01:15:32,403 --> 01:15:33,609
[Anne] I am briefed appropriately.

1003
01:15:33,696 --> 01:15:35,278
[Harley] Were it in person,
I'd believe it.

1004
01:15:35,823 --> 01:15:37,234
-[Anne] I am often ill.
-[Harley] True.

1005
01:15:38,075 --> 01:15:39,065
Sadly true.

1006
01:15:39,744 --> 01:15:42,202
The war with the French will bleed us dry
even if we win.

1007
01:15:42,288 --> 01:15:43,699
We are in our strongest position now.

1008
01:15:43,789 --> 01:15:47,032
If Marlborough loses this next battle,
we could lose all.

1009
01:15:48,377 --> 01:15:50,038
The people hate the war, you realize,

1010
01:15:50,629 --> 01:15:51,664
they begin to hate you.

1011
01:15:53,591 --> 01:15:55,832
Lady Marlborough has not told you
of the riots in Leeds?

1012
01:15:56,510 --> 01:15:57,500
[Anne] No, she has not.

1013
01:15:58,804 --> 01:16:01,466
- All I ask is that you search your heart.
- Of course.

1014
01:16:01,557 --> 01:16:03,173
Not Lady Marlborough's heart, your own.

1015
01:16:03,934 --> 01:16:06,141
I must talk to you of your maid also.

1016
01:16:06,228 --> 01:16:07,889
- Abigail?
- I believe that is her name.

1017
01:16:08,314 --> 01:16:11,022
It seems Colonel Masham has fallen
for her. He wishes to marry.

1018
01:16:11,776 --> 01:16:12,766
[Anne] She's just a maid.

1019
01:16:13,235 --> 01:16:15,351
[Harley] lt is irregular and inexplicable,

1020
01:16:15,446 --> 01:16:17,858
but being sentimental,
I am moved to help if possible.

1021
01:16:22,620 --> 01:16:23,826
What do you mean she's not been seen?

1022
01:16:24,789 --> 01:16:28,077
[Masham] She took a horse, Your Majesty.
It did not come back and nor did she.

1023
01:16:29,460 --> 01:16:30,791
[Godolphin] I shall send riders.

1024
01:16:33,714 --> 01:16:34,545
No.

1025
01:16:35,424 --> 01:16:37,882
I think she means to vex me.
Do not send riders.

1026
01:16:38,511 --> 01:16:39,842
[Godolphin]
In case she has fallen, though.

1027
01:16:39,929 --> 01:16:41,511
She's too good a rider for that.

1028
01:16:41,597 --> 01:16:43,884
I know what she is. Do not seek her.

1029
01:16:52,942 --> 01:16:55,104
[grunting and groaning]

1030
01:16:59,406 --> 01:17:00,487
Where am I?

1031
01:17:01,283 --> 01:17:02,273
You're in heaven.

1032
01:17:03,494 --> 01:17:05,656
That's God. You'll meet him later.

1033
01:17:09,416 --> 01:17:11,874
- I must go.
- I don't think that's happening.

1034
01:17:17,883 --> 01:17:18,873
[woman] Lie back.

1035
01:17:23,347 --> 01:17:24,837
[inhales sharply]

1036
01:17:24,932 --> 01:17:26,047
[woman] Stop infection.

1037
01:17:37,945 --> 01:17:39,185
[Anne] Get Lady Marlborough.

1038
01:17:40,573 --> 01:17:42,689
Now! Take me to her!

1039
01:17:53,252 --> 01:17:54,458
Find her.

1040
01:17:58,507 --> 01:18:00,669
Find her!

1041
01:18:14,023 --> 01:18:15,889
[Anne] There are wolves out there,
are there not?

1042
01:18:15,983 --> 01:18:18,566
[Godolphin] No, Your Majesty.
I don't think so.

1043
01:18:18,652 --> 01:18:21,110
Perhaps she's gone to Blenheim,
her palace?

1044
01:18:21,197 --> 01:18:23,404
There is no palace yet. It is the woods.

1045
01:18:23,490 --> 01:18:24,980
We should check in the trees,
just to be sure.

1046
01:18:25,075 --> 01:18:26,065
[Anne] Mr. Harley!

1047
01:18:26,410 --> 01:18:27,616
I apologize.

1048
01:18:27,703 --> 01:18:29,444
I hope we find her,
and she's not dead in a ditch.

1049
01:18:29,914 --> 01:18:31,530
The business of state, however,
cannot stop.

1050
01:18:31,624 --> 01:18:35,788
Your Majesty, there has been no word
from the front in two weeks.

1051
01:18:35,878 --> 01:18:38,040
There is no doubt
that Marlborough is in trouble.

1052
01:18:38,714 --> 01:18:41,046
We need to send a division immediately
to help him.

1053
01:18:41,133 --> 01:18:44,251
Costing a fortune, built on your paranoia,
and walking into God knows what.

1054
01:18:44,595 --> 01:18:46,336
We need to wait.

1055
01:18:46,430 --> 01:18:48,467
I will think on it for a while.

1056
01:18:48,557 --> 01:18:49,718
[Godolphin] This cannot wait.

1057
01:18:50,142 --> 01:18:52,224
We need to act now.

1058
01:18:52,311 --> 01:18:54,143
Is it a bit like going late to your party?

1059
01:18:55,272 --> 01:18:58,105
If the party's going well, they did not
need you, and they resent the intrusion.

1060
01:18:58,192 --> 01:19:00,524
But if it's going badly,
you cannot save it,

1061
01:19:00,611 --> 01:19:03,854
and you tend to regret
ever putting on your nice gown for it.

1062
01:19:04,281 --> 01:19:06,238
[Godolphin] It is not like a party.

1063
01:19:06,325 --> 01:19:07,986
[Abigail] I'm sorry, Prime Minister,
a passing thought.

1064
01:19:08,077 --> 01:19:09,408
I think it is like a party.

1065
01:19:09,495 --> 01:19:11,486
- A perfect analogy.
-[Anne] We will wait.

1066
01:19:11,705 --> 01:19:14,538
Make sure they have their best dresses on
so they're ready at a moment's notice.

1067
01:19:14,708 --> 01:19:17,040
Shift a division to the coast
and have a boat at the ready.

1068
01:19:23,175 --> 01:19:24,165
Abigail.

1069
01:19:25,511 --> 01:19:27,001
I worry something has befallen her.

1070
01:19:27,680 --> 01:19:29,136
It's night. Out there alone.

1071
01:19:30,182 --> 01:19:31,217
[Abigail] She's strong.

1072
01:19:32,142 --> 01:19:33,678
- And she'll be fine.
- Yes.

1073
01:19:34,812 --> 01:19:36,473
She saved me my whole life.

1074
01:19:37,273 --> 01:19:38,604
Without her, I'm nothing.

1075
01:19:38,691 --> 01:19:39,931
That is not true.

1076
01:19:40,901 --> 01:19:43,063
- You are the queen.
-I'm tired.

1077
01:19:43,445 --> 01:19:45,436
It hurts. Everything hurts.

1078
01:19:45,531 --> 01:19:46,817
Everyone leaves me.

1079
01:19:48,200 --> 01:19:49,281
Dies.

1080
01:19:49,368 --> 01:19:50,529
Finally her.

1081
01:19:52,997 --> 01:19:54,863
If she's not dead, I will cut her throat.

1082
01:19:55,457 --> 01:19:57,198
She may be doing this to hurt me,

1083
01:19:57,543 --> 01:19:59,705
make me dissolve and dissemble.
I will not.

1084
01:19:59,795 --> 01:20:02,628
She will be fine. They will find her.

1085
01:20:02,715 --> 01:20:04,001
[Anne] I don't care.

1086
01:20:04,091 --> 01:20:06,628
You are a beautiful person.

1087
01:20:07,469 --> 01:20:09,051
You glow with loveliness.

1088
01:20:11,348 --> 01:20:12,338
We will marry you.

1089
01:20:12,933 --> 01:20:14,970
- What?
- Colonel Masham wishes to marry you.

1090
01:20:15,436 --> 01:20:17,177
- He does?
- Yes, you've quite captured him.

1091
01:20:18,939 --> 01:20:20,020
That is absurd.

1092
01:20:21,525 --> 01:20:22,936
I have nothing to offer.

1093
01:20:23,027 --> 01:20:26,019
I'm a penniless servant.
It would be career suicide for him.

1094
01:20:26,113 --> 01:20:28,571
Your first thought is for him?
Oh, you are a darling.

1095
01:20:28,657 --> 01:20:29,818
I care for him.

1096
01:20:31,368 --> 01:20:32,904
Not in the way I care for you,

1097
01:20:33,579 --> 01:20:34,660
but enough to marry.

1098
01:20:35,664 --> 01:20:37,951
I will not lie,
I would like to be a lady again.

1099
01:20:38,042 --> 01:20:39,578
Yes, yes, this is right.

1100
01:20:39,668 --> 01:20:40,578
While she is gone.

1101
01:20:40,669 --> 01:20:43,411
If we wait, she'll return
and yell and stomp about it.

1102
01:20:43,505 --> 01:20:45,917
But you must have this. This is my gift
to you, and I demand you take it.

1103
01:20:46,008 --> 01:20:46,918
Of course. When--

1104
01:20:47,009 --> 01:20:47,999
Let's-- Now.

1105
01:20:48,093 --> 01:20:50,209
[classical music playing]

1106
01:20:50,304 --> 01:20:56,050
I, Abigail Hill, take thee, Samuel Masham,
to be my lawful wedded husband.

1107
01:20:56,143 --> 01:21:02,105
[Masham] I, Samuel Masham, take thee,
Abigail Hill, to be my lawful wedded wife.

1108
01:21:02,191 --> 01:21:04,899
[Clapping]

1109
01:21:05,611 --> 01:21:06,772
[Abigail] It is most generous.

1110
01:21:07,237 --> 01:21:08,318
I am overwhelmed.

1111
01:21:08,405 --> 01:21:10,191
Shall we say "gambling debts," Mr. Harley?

1112
01:21:10,282 --> 01:21:11,272
Excellent.

1113
01:21:11,367 --> 01:21:13,153
[Anne] Oh, and you are to take apartments
in the east wing.

1114
01:21:13,243 --> 01:21:15,154
-[Masham] Thank you, Your Majesty.
-[Abigail] Thank you.

1115
01:21:15,245 --> 01:21:16,735
[Anne] Oh, it is fun
to be queen sometimes.

1116
01:21:16,830 --> 01:21:18,616
[Harley] Hmm. One can only imagine.

1117
01:21:18,707 --> 01:21:20,368
[music continues]

1118
01:21:20,459 --> 01:21:22,416
[Masham] You're looking the wrong way.

1119
01:21:22,503 --> 01:21:25,120
Where could she have gone?
You sent riders looking for her?

1120
01:21:25,214 --> 01:21:26,955
[Masham] I have told you before.

1121
01:21:27,049 --> 01:21:29,461
She would be sick for several days,
but she would be near recovered by now.

1122
01:21:29,551 --> 01:21:31,713
[Masham] She probably went back
to Southampton.

1123
01:21:31,804 --> 01:21:34,296
To do what? To plan what? To get ready?

1124
01:21:34,390 --> 01:21:37,633
I am as hard as a rock,
and it is our wedding night.

1125
01:21:44,566 --> 01:21:45,522
Lie still.

1126
01:21:46,944 --> 01:21:47,775
[Masham grunts]

1127
01:21:58,539 --> 01:22:01,782
Now that she is gone, I find myself
more concerned than when she was here.

1128
01:22:03,001 --> 01:22:05,493
For it is like she could strike
from anywhere at any time,

1129
01:22:05,587 --> 01:22:07,043
and I will not see it coming.

1130
01:22:07,589 --> 01:22:09,125
[Masham exhales]

1131
01:22:10,717 --> 01:22:11,752
I must be calm.

1132
01:22:12,803 --> 01:22:13,793
She's gone.

1133
01:22:14,388 --> 01:22:15,378
I'm married.

1134
01:22:16,265 --> 01:22:17,096
[Masham groans]

1135
01:22:17,391 --> 01:22:18,301
But I must be ready.

1136
01:22:18,392 --> 01:22:21,054
And yet, how to be ready
when I do not know where my enemy is?

1137
01:22:22,896 --> 01:22:26,355
My life is like a maze
I continually think I have gotten out of,

1138
01:22:26,775 --> 01:22:29,062
only to find another corner
right in front of me.

1139
01:22:29,987 --> 01:22:32,854
[Masham groans]

1140
01:22:34,450 --> 01:22:36,441
[music ends]

1141
01:22:39,997 --> 01:22:43,115
-[rhythmic creaking]
-[muffled moaning]

1142
01:22:45,169 --> 01:22:47,160
Boy, fetch me a carriage.

1143
01:22:48,338 --> 01:22:49,794
Mae says no.

1144
01:22:50,632 --> 01:22:52,964
I'm leaving. Help me up.

1145
01:22:58,223 --> 01:22:59,338
Mae says no.

1146
01:23:03,562 --> 01:23:04,802
Are you feeling better, then?

1147
01:23:04,897 --> 01:23:06,979
[Sarah] ls my horse alive,
or did you eat it?

1148
01:23:07,065 --> 01:23:08,180
I sold it.

1149
01:23:09,067 --> 01:23:10,353
You still owe me, though.

1150
01:23:12,029 --> 01:23:13,986
You can suck for your supper from now on.

1151
01:23:14,072 --> 01:23:15,562
I'll take 20%.

1152
01:23:16,825 --> 01:23:19,442
You seem posh. Gents will like that.

1153
01:23:20,078 --> 01:23:22,194
[Sarah] Have you ever seen
ten gold sovereigns?

1154
01:23:22,748 --> 01:23:24,034
[Mae] In my dreams.

1155
01:23:24,249 --> 01:23:26,365
[Sarah] Go to Hyde Park fountain
at 9:00 in the morning,

1156
01:23:26,460 --> 01:23:28,326
and you will see a man walking a duck.

1157
01:23:33,800 --> 01:23:34,631
[Godolphin chuckles]

1158
01:23:35,344 --> 01:23:37,585
What happened? Are you all right?

1159
01:23:37,679 --> 01:23:40,296
That cunt, Abigail, poisoned me.

1160
01:23:40,390 --> 01:23:42,427
Mary Magdalene here found me.

1161
01:23:44,102 --> 01:23:45,137
Did they rape you?

1162
01:23:45,729 --> 01:23:47,311
No, they didn't.

1163
01:23:47,940 --> 01:23:50,398
But gainful employment is on offer
should I need it.

1164
01:23:50,484 --> 01:23:52,145
[Godolphin] Abigail did this?

1165
01:23:52,361 --> 01:23:53,192
Yes.

1166
01:23:54,279 --> 01:23:55,269
How goes the kingdom?

